<br>
Now the game: its set in kind of a midevil era with the usual hordes of Goblins and Orcs fighting you around each corner. Its pretty much a hack and slash, but you can switch from 3rd to 1st person at any time, so it can be played much like an FPS if thats more your style. The graphics are pretty good, definitely xbox-worthy, no blocky characters, or aliasing, with excellent textures, REALLY nice textures. I think there is bumb-mapping because i read about that somewhere, but i really cant tell... Controls use pretty much the same ones as Halo, left stick to look around, right to strafe etc. and are nice and tight. No changing the sensitivity of the look-analog though, which some of you might not like, i think its just fine though. A nice touch to the game is that you collect gold throughout the levels and buy items, that you cant or didnt collect in-game, before missions. A pretty nice selection of items, weapons mostly, ranging from maces to bows to swords, but that brings me to the single biggest flaw in the game, and a pretty big one i think: <br>
<br>
THE TEXT IS ALMOST IMPOSSIBLE TO READ!<br>
now this wouldnt have been a bad thing if there was only text in the cut scenes, seeing as those are voiced, but it is extremely difficult to read menus, missions, and item descriptions. This one flaw adds to a lot of frustration when you really dont want to spend the time deciphering your missions when you should be able to just read the damn things!<br>
<br>
overall though, the game is decent, and pretty fun, with two different campaigns to play and a nice atmosphere to play in. <br>
i give it a 4/5 <p><BR>
